Hokkaido Takushoku Bank Ltd is launching100 mln Swiss francs of convertible notes due September 30,1992, indicated at 1-1/4 pct and par, lead manager Swiss BankCorp said.    Pricing and conversion terms will be fixed on April 19 andpayment date is April 30. Interest is payable half-yearly.    Early redemption is possible from March 31, 1990 at 104pct, declining by one point per half-year thereafter, and fortax reasons from 1988 at 102 pct, declining by 1/2 pointannually thereafter. REUTER&#3;